==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neo-Scholasticism
<hw>Ne`o-Scho*las"ti*cism</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The modern revival of
the Scholastic philosophy, esp. of that of <person>Thomas
Aquinas</person>, with critical revision to suit the exigencies of the
general advance in learning. The Neo-Scholastic movement received a
great impetus from <person>Leo XIII.</person>'s interest in
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neossine</ent>⟦br⟧
